snippet: The target of the strike by the Israeli military, a Palestinian militant accused of firing rockets into Israel, was critically wounded, along with a bystander.
abstract: Israeli military says it has carried out airstrike against Abdallah Kharti, Palestinian militant in Gaza responsible for firing rockets into Israel; strike, which critically wounded Kharti, marks return to practice known as 'targeted killing' that had all but halted after cease fire declared over 14 months ago.

byline.contributor: Fares Akram contributed reporting from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: The target of the strike by the Israeli military, a Palestinian militant accused of firing rockets into Israel, was critically wounded, along with a bystander.

headline.main: Israel Orders Airstrike Against Gaza Militant
